title: For Sale:  AR 15 SP1 SERIAL #23228  1972 YEAR OF MANUFACTURE
postcontent:
WARNING:  BEWARE OF FRAUD LISTING FOR AN AR 15 SP1 IN UTAH.

I was enticed into negotiating a sale for a 1972 Colt AR 15 SP1 .223 Cal 99.9%.  The fraudulent seller claims the unit is serial #23228, has only been fired once, includes a Colt 20 round magazine and a Kay Industries 30 round magazine.  Price was $930.00.  The ad includes photos which were stolen from the actual item which was sold back in Oct., 2013.  The photos show a rifle on a wooden block.

I became suspicious when she, (Sherri Bringard), would not supply me a phone number or address.  And, she requested I send her brother, (in another state), payment as he "really needed the money".  I immediately googled her name and learned she had tried this scam advertisement in October, 2013.

I am contacting the ATF and the local police department in Delta, Utah where it appears the woman is located.

I looked for a means to contact this website, for the purpose of informing them of this issue, however, I was unable to locate such.  I hope a moderator will make any necessary adjustments to my post.
